{
  "stem": "6878.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "While we were young people, we didn't feel a bad anti-Semitism, but occasionally we went-- we went in with a fight with some Lithuanian people.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like, example, I was a member of the fire brigade in, in the Krekenova.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In wintertime, we used to make ice skate rinks, chop out little holes in the ice, and plant little trees around, and that was the ice rink.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We used to charge 20 cents for, for ice skating.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one day, from the Lithuanian school, there were a number of students, and they started to, to fight with me and my brother, Simon.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were quite tough guys, the two of us, and we took off the ice skates, and we gave them a good hiding with the ice skates.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were called in by the police to apologize to them because some of them got hurt badly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But when we appeared before the headmaster of the school, and he ask us what brought us to the fight, and when I said to them that they called us [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That means [INAUDIBLE], like [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE], and then we start fighting.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They started to push us around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Obviously, we didn't look just to-- with our heads down.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We fight back.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And if this is the case, he says, you can go back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's our student's fault and the students were actually prosecuted, not us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was in the transport business.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had a horse and cart, and he used to transport grain from Krekenova to Ponevezh.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was the capital there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was 30 kilometers, dirt road.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The people, used to-- they used to walk, not sit on the wagon, but they used to walk past-- past the road and walk right through the night to it.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
